<div class="heroContainer">
    <div class="spacerDivBig"></div>
    <div class="heroCTA" onclick="location.href = '/product/pricing';">
        <div class="heroCTATitle">New</div>
        <p>Cloudy.NET v1.0: Try it</p>
        <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="spacerDivSmall"></div>
    <h1>Build bespoke<br /><span id="cycler">back offices</span><br class="heroBreak" /> in &lt;6 min</h1>
    <div class="spacerDivSmall"></div>
    <div class="heroImg">
        <img src="~/assets/images/cloudy_ui.png" alt="Cloudy UI" width="300" height="187.11" />
    </div>
</div>

<div id="businessTitle" class="containerTitle">
    <h2>Why agencies use Cloudy</h2>
</div>
<div class="uspContainer">
    <div class="uspDiv block">
        <h3>Deliver more projects</h3>
        <p>Free your team from spending significant time to build and maintain back offices. Instead, focus on delivering the creative solutions that drive your business forward.</p>
        <i class="fa-solid fa-rocket fa-2x"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="uspDiv block">
        <h3>Write and maintain less code</h3>
        <p>You can build a basic CRUD application with &lt;150 lines of code. Cloudy utilises standard components so you can build what you need with as few arguments as possible.</p>
        <i class="fa-solid fa-martini-glass-citrus fa-2x"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="uspDiv block">
        <h3>Make your staff happier</h3>
        <p>Cloudy plays with your system instead of you with ours. Focus on writing your business logic, spend minimum time on integration.</p>
        <i class="fa-solid fa-hand-holding-heart fa-2x"></i>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="pricingTitle" class="containerTitle">
    <h2>Features</h2>
</div>
<div class="featureContainer">
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-file-code fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Code-first data model</h3>
        <p>Data model stored declaratively, version controlled, deployed with your app.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-cubes fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Hybrid-headless - use as headless, coupled or both</h3>
        <p>You decide. Combine, extend, whatever gets you going.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-language fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Scan EF Core to create content types</h3>
        <p>Design your data model, Cloudy interprets the entities.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Advanced state manager</h3>
        <p>Track unsaved changes and reconciliate conflicts.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-people-arrows fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Conflict resolution assistant</h3>
        <p>Notification of conflicts and suggestions to solve them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-shapes fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Build with blocks across pages and views</h3>
        <p>Embed single blocks, link blocks across other blocks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-database fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Built in support for any database in EF Core</h3>
        <p>Literally anything. Inmemory, SQLite, SQL Server, CosmosDB...</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass-arrow-right fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Search, sort, filter your entities</h3>
        <p>Find things easily and intuitively.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-pen-to-square fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Custom columns and edit field controls</h3>
        <p>An edit environment you design.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-photo-film fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Media picker</h3>
        <p>Select any file right from the admin UI.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-square-plus fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>CRUD application</h3>
        <p>Manage your entities easily from the admin UI.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-brain fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Expressive admin UI</h3>
        <p>Cloudy reads and interprets whatever you do.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="featureDiv block">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-up-a-z fa-2x"></i>
        <h3>Automated naming support</h3>
        <p>Pluralisation of your entities in the admin UI.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="nextFeature featureDiv block" onclick="window.location.href = 'mailto:hello@cloudy.net?subject=Featureeeeeeeeee';">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus fa-4x"></i>
        <h3>What should we work on next?</h3>
    </div>
</div>

